<doc>
  <member name="D3D10_STATE_BLOCK_MASK">
    <summary>
      <para>Indicates the device state.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>A state-block mask indicates the device states that a pass or a technique changes.  The <see cref="D3D10StateBlockMaskEnableCapture" /> function provides a convenient way of setting a range of bitmasks for the array members of <b>D3D10_STATE_BLOCK_MASK</b>.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d10/d3d10-graphics-reference-d3d10-core-structures">Core Structures</seealso>
  </member>
